This paper deals with power control in MC-CDMA systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The paper also proposes a game-theoretic approach to power control, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance improvement achieved through the proposed approach, which could be considered as a multimedia (cs.MM) application.
